The paper deals with the problem of ranking items based on incomplete and noisy pairwise comparisons, which is a common problem in data analysis, computer vision, and machine learning. The paper proposes a synchronization-based approach to this problem, which involves finding a consistent ranking that satisfies the given pairwise comparisons. This approach involves techniques from linear algebra, optimization, and graph theory, which are all relevant to several subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
